\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Effect of inverse temperature $\beta $ on position selection probability for eight candidate positions with varying utility. At low $\beta $, the distribution is nearly uniform (exploratory). At high $\beta $, probability concentrates on the highest-utility position $p_5$ (greedy). Intermediate $\beta $ balances exploration and exploitation.}}{4}{figure.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:boltzmann}{{2}{4}{Effect of inverse temperature $\beta $ on position selection probability for eight candidate positions with varying utility. At low $\beta $, the distribution is nearly uniform (exploratory). At high $\beta $, probability concentrates on the highest-utility position $p_5$ (greedy). Intermediate $\beta $ balances exploration and exploitation}{figure.2}{}}
